    "longBusinessSummary": "The Great Eastern Shipping Company Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in the shipping and offshore businesses in India and internationally. The company is involved in the transportation of crude oil, petroleum products, and gas and dry bulk commodities. It operates a fleet of 41 vessels comprising 27 tankers, including 5 crude carriers, 17 product carriers, and 5 LPG carriers; and 14 dry bulk carriers comprising 2 capesize, 9 kamsarmax, 2 supramax, and an ultramax with an aggregating 3.25 million dwt. The company also offers offshore oilfield services, which include the ownership and/or operation of offshore supply vessels and mobile offshore drilling rigs. The Great Eastern Shipping Company Limited was incorporated in 1948 and is based in Mumbai, India.",
